### -- Variables -------------------------------------------------------
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8180
@apiUrl      = http://localhost:8080
@realm       = ajudafio
@clientId    = ajudafio-frontend

# Test user — must exist in Keycloak (create via http://localhost:8180 → realm ajudafio)
@username = test@ajudafio.com
@password = Test@123


### 0 — Health Check (no auth required)
GET {{apiUrl}}/health


###

### 1 — Login (Resource Owner Password Credentials)
# @name login
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username={{username}}&password={{password}}


###

### 2 — Keycloak UserInfo  (resolves `sub` claim without manually decoding the JWT)
# @name userinfo
GET {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/userinfo
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access_token}}


###

### 3 — GET /auth/me  (direct API — in production KrakenD injects X-User-* from the JWT)
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/me
X-User-Id:    {{userinfo.response.body.$.sub}}
X-User-Email: {{username}}
X-User-Name:  {{userinfo.response.body.$.preferred_username}}
X-User-Roles: CLIENT


###

### 4 — GET /auth/me/accounts
GET {{apiUrl}}/auth/me/accounts
X-User-Id:    {{userinfo.response.body.$.sub}}
X-User-Email: {{username}}
X-User-Name:  {{userinfo.response.body.$.preferred_username}}
X-User-Roles: CLIENT


###

### 5 — Refresh Token
# @name refresh
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=refresh_token&client_id={{clientId}}&refresh_token={{login.response.body.$.refresh_token}}


###

### 6 — Logout (invalidates the refresh token)
POST {{keycloakUrl}}/realms/{{realm}}/protocol/openid-connect/logout
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{clientId}}&refresh_token={{login.response.body.$.refresh_token}}
